      "extra": {
        "message": "Debug Mode Enabled via Environment Variable\n\nThe DEBUG environment variable is passed to the application container. Given the application context confirms debug mode is enabled, this propagates a debug configuration to a public-facing deployment. Debug mode typically exposes detailed error messages, stack traces, and potentially interactive debuggers.\n\nImpact: Attackers can obtain detailed internal application information including stack traces, source code paths, and potentially gain interactive code execution through debug consoles.\n\nFix: Remove the DEBUG environment variable or explicitly set it to a falsy value (e.g., DEBUG=0 or DEBUG=false) in production deployments.",
